article.headline: La Salle 78, N.J. Tech 59
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Rodney Green scored 18 points and Ruben Guillandeaux added 12 as La Salle defeated New Jersey Tech 78-59 Tuesday night. Yves Mekongo Mbala added 10 points and eight rebounds for La Salle (8-9), which posted a 44-25 rebounding edge. Kraig Peters scored 18 points and Clayton Barker 16 for the Highlanders (3-15), who are playing their first season at the Division I level. The Explorers led by as many as 22 points in the first half before NJIT rallied within 58-50 on two free throws by Peters with 10:45 left to play. La Salle then went on a 14-2 run to build a 72-50 advantage with 4:32 remaining, and NJIT never threatened again.
